{"title_page": "List of radio stations in Africa", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{More citations needed|date=August 2018}}\nThis is a '''list of [[radio station]]s in [[Africa]]'''. For countries for which information is not listed, please see the \"Media\" section of that country's national article, or use the \"Media in Africa\" box at the bottom of this article.\n\n==Algeria==\n{{see also|Media of Algeria}}\n\n[[Entreprise nationale de Radiodiffusion sonore]] or ENRS is the state [[Public broadcasting|public]] radio broadcaster of Algeria, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[Alger Cha\u00eene 1]] (Arabic)\n* [[Alger Cha\u00eene 2]] (Berber)\n* [[Alger Cha\u00eene 3]] (French)\n* [[Entreprise nationale de Radiodiffusion sonore|Radio Alg\u00e9rie Internationale]]\n* [[Radio Bahdja]]\n* [[Radio Culture]]\n* [[Radio Coran]]\n* [[Jil FM]]\n* 46 local radio stations of ENRS\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Angola==\n{{see also|Media of Angola}}\n\n[[R\u00e1dio Nacional de Angola]] or RNA, is the state radio broadcaster of Angola, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n*[[Canal A (Angola)|Canal A]]\n*R\u00e1dio Luanda\n*FM Est\u00e9reo\n*N'Gola Yetu\n*R\u00e1dio 5\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Ecclesia FM - 97.5 FM Luanda (Religious Radio Station)\n* Luanda Antena Comercial - 95.5 FM Luanda\n* Ngola Radio - 87.7 FM Luanda\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Ascension Island==\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n*[[American Forces Network|AFN Ascension]]\n*[[BBC World Service]]\n*[[BFBS Radio]]\n*[[Saint fm community radio]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Benin==\n[[Office de Radiodiffusion et T\u00e9l\u00e9vision du B\u00e9nin]] or ORTB is the state broadcaster of Benin, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Radio B\u00e9nin (National)\n* Radio R\u00e9gionale\n* Atlantic FM\n* Radio Parakou\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[BBC World Service|BBC WS Africa]]\n* CAPP FM\n* FM Ou\u00e9m\u00e9\n* Radio Adja Ou\u00e8r\u00e8\n* Radio Maranatha\n* Radio Tokpa\n* [[Radio France Internationale|RFI Afrique]]\n* RIC (Radio Immacul\u00e9e Conception)\n* Golfe FM\n* Oc\u00e9an FM\n* Soleil FM\n* Frissons Radio\n* Fraternit\u00e9 FM\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Botswana==\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Duma FM\n* Gabz FM\n* [[Radio Botswana]] | Radio Botswana 1 & Radio Botswana 2 (FM 103)\n* [[Yarona FM]] 106.6\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Burkina Faso==\n{{see also|Media of Burkina Faso#Radio}}\n[[Radio T\u00e9l\u00e9vision du Burkina|Radio Television du Burkina]] (RTB), is the state broadcaster of Burkina Faso, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* RTB Radio (National radio station)\n* Radio Canal Arc-en-Ciel\n* ''Local RTB radio stations''\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n*[[BBC World Service|BBC WS Africa]]\n*[[Horizon FM]]\n*[[Ouaga FM]]\n*[[Radio France Internationale|RFI Afrique]]\n* Radio Gambidi\n* Radio La Voix des Lacs\n*[[Radio Maria]]\n* Radio Munyu\n* Radio Pulsar\n*[[Radio Salankoloto]]\n* Savane FM\n*[[VOA|VOA Africa]]\n* Hit Radio Burkina\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Burundi==\n{{see also|Media of Burundi}}\n[[Radio T\u00e9l\u00e9vision Nationale du Burundi]] or RTNB, is the state broadcaster of Burundi, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* RTNB Radio 1\n* RTNB Radio 2\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[BBC World Service|BBC World Service Africa]]\n* [[Bonesha FM]]\n* CCIB FM\n* [[Radio Isanganiro]]\n* [[Radio Maria]]\n* Radio Rema FM\n* Radio Scolaire Nderagakura\n* Renaissance FM\n* [[Radio France Internationale|RFI Afrique]]\n* [[Radio Publique Africaine|RPA]]\n* {{illm|Radio Umwizero|fr}}\n* Hit Radio Burundi ([https://web.archive.org/web/20110224135956/http://hitradio.ma/ Official website])\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Cameroon==\n{{see also|Media of Cameroon#Radio}}\n[[Cameroon Radio & Television]] or CRTV, is the state broadcaster of Cameroon, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* CRTV Radio Nationale\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Abakwa FM\n* [[BBC World Service|BBC WS Africa]]\n* [[Radio Bonne Nouvelle|RBN]]\n* [[Radio France Internationale|RFI Afrique]]\n* Sweet FM\n* Stone FM community Radio Ndop\n* Magic FM\n* RSI \n* Balafon FM\n* Equinoxe FM\n* CRTV radio\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Cape Verde==\n{{see also|List of radio stations in Cape Verde}}\n[[RTC (Cape Verde)|R\u00e1dio e Televis\u00e3o de Cabo Verde]] or RTC, is the state broadcaster of Cape Verde, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* RCV R\u00e1dio de Cabo Verde (National)\n* RCV Mais\n* RCV Regional\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Emissora Crist\u00e3o R\u00e1dio Nova\n*[[R\u00e1dio Barlavento]]\n*[[R\u00e1dio Clube do Mindelo]]\n* Radio Crioula FM\n* R\u00e1dio Educativa\n* R\u00e1dio Rural Santo Ant\u00e3o\n*[[RDP \u00c1frica]]\n* [[Radio France Internationale|RFI Afrique]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Central African Republic==\n{{see also|Media of the Central African Republic}}\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[BBC World Service|BBC WS Africa]]\n* Radio Centrafrique (National)\n* [[Radio Maria]]\n* Radio Ndeke Luka\n* Radio Siriri\n* [[Radio France Internationale|RFI Afrique]]\n* [[Voice of America|VOA Africa]]\n* Hit Radio RCA\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Chad==\n{{see also|Media of Chad#Radio}}\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[Radiodiffusion Nationale Tchadienne]] or RNT, is the state broadcaster of Chad.\n* [[BBC World Service|BBC WS Africa]]\n*[[DJA FM]] - ''[[N'Djamena]]''\n* [[Radio France Internationale|RFI Afrique]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Comoros==\n[[Office de Radio et T\u00e9l\u00e9vision des Comores]] or ORTC, is the state broadcaster of Comoros, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Radio Comores\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[Radio France Internationale|RFI Afrique]]\n* Tropic FM\n* Star FM\n* Sud Radio\n{{div col end}}\n\n==C\u00f4te d'Ivoire==\n[[Radiodiffusion-T\u00e9l\