cco==\n{{see also|Media of Morocco#Radio}}\n[[Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 Nationale de Radiodiffusion et de T\u00e9l\u00e9vision]] or SNRT is the state broadcaster of Morocco, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Cha\u00eene Nationale\n* Cha\u00eene Inter\n* SNRT Quran\n* SNRT Arabic\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[Atlantic Radio]]\n* [[Cap Radio (Morocco)|Cap Radio]]\n* Casa FM\n* Chada FM\n* [[Hit Radio (Morocco)|Hit Radio]]\n* Luxe Radio\n* [[M\u00e9di 1]]\n* M\u00e9dina FM\n* MED Radio\n* MFM\n* [[Radio 2M]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Mozambique==\n[[R\u00e1dio Mo\u00e7ambique]] is the state broadcaster of Mozambique, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Antena Nacional\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* 99FM\n* [[BBC World Service|BBC WS Africa]]\n* [[LM Radio]]\n* Radio \u00cdndico\n* [[Radio Maria]]\n* [[RDP \u00c1frica]]\n* [[Radio France Internationale|RFI Portugu\u00eas (\u00c1frica)]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Namibia==\n{{see also|Media of Namibia#Radio}}\n[[Namibian Broadcasting Corporation]] or NBC, is the state broadcaster of Namibia, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* NBC National Radio 1 (English)\n* NBC National Radio 2 (Afrikaans)\n* NBC National Radio 3 (German)\n* including ''Other radio stations of NBC operate in several local languages''\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[Hitradio Namibia]]: first commercial German-language radio station in Namibia, broadcasting in the central and coastal areas as well as by a live stream.\n* [[Kanaal 7/Channel 7|Channel 7]]: Broadcasting on 104.5 FM in Windhoek.  Christian community station.  The widest reach (number of transmitters throughout the country) of any Namibian radio station (except Namibian Broadcasting Corporation).\n* [[Katutura Community Radio]]: Broadcasts on 106.2 FM in Windhoek. Community radio station based in a Windhoek suburb - Katutura.\n* [[Kudu FM]]\n* Omulunga Radio\n* 99FM: English medium, commercial radio station. ([www.99fm.com.na Official website])\n* Radio Energy 100FM\n* [[Radio France Internationale|RFI Afrique]]: Broadcasting on 107.9 FM in Windhoek.  Relay of French speaking radio channel in Windhoek\n* [[UNAM Radio]]: Community Radio broadcast from [[University of Namibia]] on 97.4 FM only within the city of [[Windhoek]] and surrounding areas\n* West Coast FM: Broadcasting on 107.7 FM in [[Swakopmund]] and 106.9 FM in [[Walvis Bay]]. The only station in the [[Erongo Region]] broadcasting live, 24/7 from Swakopmund. Adult contemporary with a touch of local. Visit [http://www.westcoastfmnamibia.com www.westcoastfmnamibia.com] for further information and to listen online.\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Niger==\n{{see also|Media of Niger#Radio}}\n[[Office of Radio and Television of Niger|Office de Radiodiffusion-T\u00e9l\u00e9vision du Niger]] or ORTN, is the state broadcaster of Niger, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[Voix du Sahel]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[Anfani FM]]\n* [[BBC World Service|BBC WS Africa]]\n* [[Radio France Internationale|RFI Afrique]]\n* Saraounia FM\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Nigeria==\n{{main|List of radio stations in Nigeria}}\n* XMRadio1 ([http://xmradio1.com/ Official website]) (New music, digital audio contents and new age radio shows)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://xmradio1.listen2myradio.com/|title=XMRadio1, discover new music & new onAIR audio content and radio shows|website=Xmradio1.listen2myradio.com|language=en|access-date=2017-07-19}}</ref>\n* 234Radio ([http://www.234radio.com Official website]) (Internet Radio; Broadcasting from Nigeria, UK, USA and Jamaica, its also available on Android<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.TTFRadio.Radioone&hl=en_GB |title=Archived copy |access-date=2017-08-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150909090738/https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.TTFRadio.Radioone&hl=en_GB |arc