4/7 volunteer driven online radio station streaming daily from Cape Town, playing all jazz from Africa including, Blues, Latin & World jazz)\n* Soweto iRadio <ref>[http://www.sowetoiradio.co.za] {{dead link|date=August 2018}}</ref>\n* 70vibe-fm - It's about the seventies music! <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.70vibe-fm.com|title=70vibe-fm|first=Mark|last=Botes-Lashmar|website=70vibe-fm|accessdate=10 August 2018}}</ref>\n{{div col end}}\n\n==South Sudan==\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[BBC World Service|BBC WS Africa]]\n* [[BBC World Service|BBC WS Arabic]]\n* Bakhita Radio (Juba)\n* Emmanuel Radio (Torit)\n* Easter Radio (Yei)\n* Voice of Hope (Wau)\n* Anisa Radio (Yambio)\n* Good News (Rumbek)\n* Sout al Mahaba (Malakal)\n* Radio Don Bosco (Torit)\n* Miraya FM\n* City FM (Juba)\n* [[Monte Carlo Doualiya]]\n* [[Radio France Internationale|RFI Afrique]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Sudan==\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Miraya FM\n* [[Radio Dabanga]]\n* SRTC Sudan Radio\n{{div col end}}\n* Voice of Peace\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}} \n** Sudan National Radio\n** FM 100\n** Salam Radio\n** Quran Radio\n** Wadi Nile Valley Radio\n{{div col end}}\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Swaziland==\n[[Swaziland Broadcasting and Information Services]] or SBIS, is the state broadcaster of Swaziland, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Radio 1 (Siswati)\n* Radio 2 (English)\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* One FM\n* [[Trans World Radio|TWR Africa]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Tanzania==\n{{see also|Media of Tanzania#Radio}}\nTanzania Broadcasting Corporation TBC, owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* TBC FM\n* TBC Taifa\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Abood Radio\n* Bongo Radio (Online Radio Station)\n* Clouds FM \n* Country FM \n* East Africa Radio\n* Ebony FM\n* HHC Alive Radio (Christian Radio)\n* Info Radio \n* Kwa Neema FM\n* Radio Kwizera FM-Covering Kagera, Kigoma, Geita, Shinyanga, Mwanza, Simiyu, Mara regions in North-West