al radio stations of ENRS\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Angola==\n{{see also|Media of Angola}}\n\n[[R\u00e1dio Nacional de Angola]] or RNA, is the state radio broadcaster of Angola, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n*[[Canal A (Angola)|Canal A]]\n*R\u00e1dio Luanda\n*FM Est\u00e9reo\n*N'Gola Yetu\n*R\u00e1dio 5\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Ecclesia FM - 97.5 FM Luanda (Religious Radio Station)\n* Luanda Antena Comercial - 95.5 FM Luanda\n* Ngola Radio - 87.7 FM Luanda\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Ascension Island==\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n*[[American Forces Network|AFN Ascension]]\n*[[BBC World Service]]\n*[[BFBS Radio]]\n*[[Saint fm community radio]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Benin==\n[[Office de Radiodiffusion et T\u00e9l\u00e9vision du B\u00e9nin]] or ORTB is the state broadcaster of Benin, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Radio B\u00e9nin (National)\n* Radio R\u00e9gionale\n* Atlantic FM\n* Radio Parakou\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[BBC World Service|BBC WS Africa]]\n* CAPP FM\n* FM Ou\u00e9m\u00e9\n* Radio Adja Ou\u00e8r\u00e8\n* Radio Maranatha\n* Radio Tokpa\n* [[Radio France Internationale|RFI Afrique]]\n* RIC (Radio Immacul\u00e9e Conception)\n* Golfe FM\n* Oc\u00e9an FM\n* Soleil FM\n* Frissons Radio\n* Fraternit\u00e9 FM\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Botswana==\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Duma FM\n* Gabz FM\n* [[Radio Botswana]] | Radio Botswana 1 & Radio Botswana 2 (FM 103)\n* [[Yarona FM]] 106.6\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Burkina Faso==\n{{see also|Media of Burkina Faso#Radio}}\n[[Radio T\u00e9l\u00e9vision du Burkina|Radio Television du Burkina]] (RTB), is the state broadcaster of Burkina Faso, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* RTB Radio (National radio station)\n* Radio Canal Arc-en-Ciel\n* ''Local RTB radio stations''\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n*[[BBC World Service|BBC WS Africa]]\n*[[Horizon FM]]\n*[[Ouaga FM]]\n*[[Radio France Internationale|RFI Afrique]]\n* Radio Gambidi\n* Radio La Voix des Lacs\n*[[Radio Maria]]\n* Radio Munyu\n* Radio Pulsar\n*[[Radio Salankoloto]]\n* Savane FM\n*[[VOA|VOA Africa]]\n* Hit Radio Burkina\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Burundi==\n{{see also|Media of Burundi}}\n[[Radio T\u00e9l\u00e9vision Nationale du Burundi]] or RTNB, is the state broadcaster of Burundi, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* RTNB Radio 1\n* RTNB Radio 2\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[BBC World Service|BBC World Service Africa]]\n* [[Bonesha FM]]\n* CCIB FM\n* [[Radio Isanganiro]]\n* [[Radio Maria]]\n* Radio Rema FM\n* Radio Scolaire Nderagakura\n* Renaissance FM\n* [[Radio France Internationale|RFI Afrique]]\n* [[Radio Publique Africaine|RPA]]\n* {{illm|Radio Umwizero|fr}}\n* Hit Radio Burundi ([https://web.archive.org/web/20110224135956/http://hitradio.ma/ Official website])\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Cameroon==\n{{see also|Media of Cameroon#Radio}}\n[[Cameroon Radio & Television]] or CRTV, is the state broadcaster of Cameroon, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* CRTV Radio Nationale\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Abakwa FM\n* [[BBC World Service|BBC WS Africa]]\n* [[Radio Bonne Nouvelle|RBN]]\n* [[Radio France Internationale|RFI Afrique]]\n* Sweet FM\n* Stone FM community Radio Ndop\n* Magic FM\n* RSI \n* Balafon FM\n* Equinoxe FM\n* CRTV radio\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Cape Verde==\n{{see also|List of radio stations in Cape Verde}}\n[[RTC (Cape Verde)|R\u00e1dio e Televis\u00e3o de Cabo Verde]] or RTC, is the state broadcaster of Cape Verde, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* RCV R\u00e1dio de Cabo Verde (National)\n* RCV Mais\n* RCV Regional\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Emissora Crist\u00e3o R\u00e1dio Nova\n*[[R\u00e1dio Barlavento]]\n*[[R\u00e1dio Clube do Mindelo]]\n* Radio Crioula FM\n* R\u00e1dio Educativa\n* R\u00e1dio Rural Santo Ant\u00e3o\n*[[RDP \u00c1frica]]\n