io Fana\n* zami 90.1 FM\n* FM Addis 96.3 FM\n* EBC 97.1 FM\n* Fana FM 98.1\n* Bisrat FM 101.1\n* Sheger FM 102.1\n* EBC FM 104.7\n* Afro FM 105.3\n* KETO 93.9 FM Denver\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Gabon==\n{{see also|Media of Gabon#Radio}}\n[[Radiodiffusion-T\u00e9l\u00e9vision Gabonaise]] or RTG, is the state broadcaster of Gabon, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* RTG Ch\u00e2ine 1\n* RTG Ch\u00e2ine 2\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[BBC World Service|BBC WS Africa]]\n* Radio Sainte-Marie\n* [[Radio France Internationale|RFI Afrique]]\n* Hit Radio Gabon\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Ghana==\n{{see also|Lists of radio stations in Ghana}}\n[[Ghana Broadcasting Corporation]] or GBC, is the state broadcaster of Ghana, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[Radio 1 (Ghana)|Radio 1]]\n* [[Radio 2 (Ghana)|Radio 2]]\n* [[Uniiq FM]]\n* [[Volta Star]] \n* [[Starr 103.5FM]] \n* [[Twin City Radio]]\n* [[Radio Central]]\n* [[Radio Savannah]]\n* [[Garden City Radio]] \n* [[URA Radio]]\n* [[Radio Upper West]]\n* [[Sunrise FM (Ghana)|Sunrise FM]]\n* [[Obonu FM]]\n* [[Radio BAR]]\n*  Atlantis Radio\n* [[BBC World Service|BBC WS Africa]]\n* Choice FM\n* [[Radio France Internationale|RFI Afrique]]\n* [[Sky FM]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Guinea==\n[[Radio T\u00e9l\u00e9vision Guin\u00e9enne]] or RTG, is the state broadcaster of Guinea, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Radio Nationale Guin\u00e9enne\n* Radio Rurale Guin\u00e9ene\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[BBC World Service|BBC WS Africa]]\n* [[NRJ Radio#The Radio Record Group|Ch\u00e9rie FM]]\n* Djoliba FM\n* Espace FM\n* \u00c9vasion FM\n* Horizon FM\n* Milo FM\n* [[Nostalgie|Nostalgie Guin\u00e9e]]\n* Radio Libert\u00e9\n* [[Radio France Internationale|RFI Afrique]]\n* Voix de l'Afrique\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Guinea-Bissau==\n{{see also|Media of Guinea-Bissau}}\n[[Guinea-Bissau National Radio and Television|Radio Televis\u00e3o da Guin\u00e9-Bissau]]