ya==\n[[Libyan Radio and Television]] or LRT, is the state broadcaster of Libya.\n*[[Al Aan FM]] (transmits in 105.3&nbsp;MHz across the country, covering cities: Al Bayda, Al Marj, Benghazi, Jadu, Misrata, Labraq, Nalut, Sabha, Sirte, Susah, Tobruk, Tripoli)\n\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[Radio Libya]]\n* [[Al-Shababiyah]]\n* [[Al-Itha'ah al-Wataniya]]\n* [[BBC World Service]]\n* [[BBC World Service|BBC WS Arabic]]\n* [[Libya FM]]\n* [[Monte Carlo Doualiya]]\n* [[Tribute FM]]\n* [[Voice of Free Libya]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Madagascar==\n{{see also|Telecommunications in Madagascar#Radio and television}}\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Radio Nationale Malagasy is the state broadcaster of Madagascar.\n* Radio Don Bosco or RDB\n* Radio Antsiva\n* [[Radio Television Analamanga]] or RTA\n** Radio Analamanga\n* Alliance FM\n* [[BBC World Service|BBC WS Africa]]\n* Fr\u00e9quence Plus\n* [[Radio France Internationale|RFI Afrique]]\n* [[Radio France Internationale|RFI Musique]]\n* Top Radio\n* [[VOA|VOA Africa]]\n* Radio Lazan'Iarivo or RLI\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Malawi==\n{{see also|Media of Malawi#Radio}}\n[[Malawi Broadcasting Corporation]] or MBC, is the state broadcaster of Malawi, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Radio 1\n* Radio 2\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* [[BBC World Service|BBC WS Africa]]\n*[[Capital Radio Malawi|Capital 102.5 FM]] - ''Nationwide''\n* Joy Radio\n* MIJ Radio\n* Power 101 FM\n* Radio Islam\n* Sawati F.M\n*[[Radio Maria]]\n*[[Star Radio Malawi|Star FM]]\n*[[Trans World Radio|TWR Africa]] - ''Nationwide''\n*[[Zodiak Broadcasting Station|ZBS]]\n{{div col end}}\n* Times radio\n* Maziko radio\n* Yoneco fm\n\n==Mali==\n{{see also|Media of Mali#Radio}}\n[[Office de Radiodiffusion Television du Mali]] or ORTM, is the state broadcaster of Mali, which owns\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Radio Mali\n* Cha\u00eene 2\n* Radio Rurale\n{{div col end}}\n\n'''Private/Other'''\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Aadar FM\