keley: University of California Press. {{ISBN|978-0-520-24892-2}} (cloth)  {{ISBN|978-0-520-25617-0}} (pbk).}}\n* {{wikicite|ref={{harvid|Bohlman|2009}}|reference=Bohlman, Philip V. (ed.). 2009. ''Jewish Musical Modernism, Old and New''. Chicago: University of Chicago Press. {{ISBN|978-0-226-06327-0}}.}}\n* {{wikicite|ref={{harvid|Botstein|n.d.}}|reference=Botstein, Leon. \"Modernism\". ''Grove Music Online'' edited by Laura Macy. <http://www.grovemusic.com> {{subscription}}.}}\n* {{wikicite|ref={{harvid|Botstein|1985}}|reference=Botstein, Leon. 1985. \"Music and Its Public: Habits of Listening and the Crisis of Musical Modernism in Vienna, 1870\u20131914\". Ph.D. thesis. Cambridge, Massachusetts: Harvard University.}}\n* {{wikicite|ref={{harvid|Bucknell|2001}}|reference=Bucknell, Brad. 2001. ''Literary Modernism and Musical Aesthetics: Pater, Pound, Joyce, and Stein''. Cambridge and New York: Cambridge University Press. {{ISBN|0-521-66028-9}}.}}\n* {{wikicite|ref={{harvid|Cavell|1976}}|reference=Cavell, Stanley. 1976. \"Music Discomposed\", in his ''Must We Mean What We Say?''{{Citation needed|date=June 2007}}<!--Inclusive pages of the essay-->. Cambridge and New York: Cambridge University Press. {{ISBN|0-521-29048-1}} (cloth), {{ISBN|0-521-21116-6}} (pbk). Updated edition, New York: Cambridge University Press, 2002. {{ISBN|0-521-82188-6}} (cloth), {{ISBN|0-521-52919-0}} (pbk).}} Cited in {{Citation needed|date=June 2007}}<!--This needs the full author's name and title of the original source, as well as the author and name of the contribution to Ashby's anthology--> ''The Pleasure of Modernist Music'', edited by, Arved Ashby, 146 n13. Rochester, NY: University of Rochester Press. {{ISBN|1-58046-143-3}}.\n* {{wikicite|ref={{harvid|Despic|2008}}|reference=Despic, Dejan, and Melita Milin (eds.). 2008. ''Rethinking Musical Modernism: Proceedings of the International Conference Held from October 11 to 13, 2007'' / ''Muzicki modernizam\u2014nova tumacenja : zbornik radov